1
00:00:43,060 --> 00:00:46,780
=Auspicious Nobles=

2
00:00:47,580 --> 00:00:49,940
=Episode 11=

3
00:00:49,940 --> 00:00:52,500
(I Am an Idol in Ancient Times)

4
00:00:58,280 --> 00:01:00,920
From a thousand hills,
birds' flights cease.

5
00:01:01,670 --> 00:01:04,680
On ten thousand paths,
human footprints vanish.

6
00:01:07,680 --> 00:01:09,760
A lone boat, an old man
in a straw cloak and hat,

7
00:01:13,790 --> 00:01:16,280
fishing alone in the cold river snow.

8
00:01:23,950 --> 00:01:25,000
Wonderful.

9
00:01:25,070 --> 00:01:26,200
This is a great poem.

10
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:31,870
Wonderful.

11
00:01:32,550 --> 00:01:33,280
Such great talent.

12
00:01:33,280 --> 00:01:34,710
As expected of the Tower Master.

13
00:01:34,840 --> 00:01:36,710
Tower Master is incredible.

14
00:01:37,680 --> 00:01:38,430
Excellent.

15
00:01:39,760 --> 00:01:42,040
"A lone boat, an old man
in a straw cloak and hat,

16
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:46,350
fishing alone in the cold river snow."

17
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:47,920
Brilliant.

18
00:01:48,310 --> 00:01:51,680
The poem employs the minimalist imagery
of thousand mountains, myriad paths,

19
00:01:51,680 --> 00:01:53,530
a lone boat, and an old man
in a straw cloak and hat,

20
00:01:53,540 --> 00:01:55,780
describing the absolute silence
of the cold river in winter

21
00:01:55,790 --> 00:01:57,070
and the aloofness of the hermit

22
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:58,680
so ethereally and magnificently.

23
00:01:58,790 --> 00:02:00,680
It's a masterpiece!

24
00:02:00,680 --> 00:02:03,480
- Tower Master!
- Tower Master!

25
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:05,920
Heavens. This is beyond
just writing a poem.

26
00:02:06,150 --> 00:02:08,280
Who would ever dare
write about river snow again?

27
00:02:08,290 --> 00:02:10,000
That would be
showing off before a master.

28
00:02:10,130 --> 00:02:12,400
The Tower Master's talent
outshines the past and present.

29
00:02:12,630 --> 00:02:14,030
Let's see who dares to defy her now.

30
00:02:14,030 --> 00:02:14,910
Exactly.

31
00:02:14,910 --> 00:02:16,190
- Exactly.
- Are you convinced?

32
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:17,150
Exactly.

33
00:02:18,030 --> 00:02:19,710
(In the ultimate desolation,)

34
00:02:20,150 --> 00:02:21,960
(she wrote of
aloofness and perseverance)

35
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:24,560
(and the noble character
between heaven and earth.)

36
00:02:25,310 --> 00:02:26,870
(She actually has such literary talent.)

37
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:29,590
(She is a formidable enemy.)

38
00:02:30,710 --> 00:02:32,000
Did you really write this poem?

39
00:02:33,300 --> 00:02:34,520
You just can't afford to lose?

40
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:37,310
Since you all refuse to accept it,

41
00:02:38,150 --> 00:02:39,710
I'll give you two more.

42
00:02:42,150 --> 00:02:43,430
Did you hear that?

43
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:45,430
Tower Master has more new works.

44
00:02:46,150 --> 00:02:46,960
Stop bragging.

45
00:02:48,590 --> 00:02:49,620
If you write another one,

46
00:02:50,010 --> 00:02:51,800
it has to be just
as good as the one before.

47
00:02:51,870 --> 00:02:52,360
Deal.

48
00:03:00,150 --> 00:03:03,400
The wind is swift, the sky is high,
and apes howl in sorrow.

49
00:03:06,030 --> 00:03:09,280
The islet is clear, the sand is white,
and birds wheel above.

50
00:03:12,310 --> 00:03:15,030
Boundless trees
shed their leaves with a rustling sigh.

51
00:03:15,750 --> 00:03:18,710
The endless Yangtze River
comes rolling on.

52
00:03:25,310 --> 00:03:28,080
Ten thousand li away,
in sad autumn, I am always a traveler.

53
00:03:28,710 --> 00:03:31,680
Sick for a century,
I climb the terrace alone.

54
00:03:32,210 --> 00:03:34,840
With hardships and bitter regrets,
my hair has turned frosty white.

55
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:39,310
Down and out, I have newly
stopped my cup of murky liquor.

56
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:40,910
Oh my...

57
00:03:41,280 --> 00:03:43,470
- Wonderful.
- This is too wonderful.

58
00:03:51,430 --> 00:03:54,150
Withered vines,
old trees, and crows at dusk.

59
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:57,960
A little bridge,
flowing water, cottages.

60
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:02,240
An ancient road,
west wind, a lean horse.

61
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:05,080
The evening sun sinks in the west,

62
00:04:06,560 --> 00:04:09,240
and the heartbroken traveler
is at the edge of the world.

63
00:04:12,470 --> 00:04:13,590
How sorrowful.

64
00:04:14,470 --> 00:04:15,360
What a great poem.

65
00:04:15,910 --> 00:04:16,560
Indeed.

66
00:04:21,040 --> 00:04:22,040
Great poem.

67
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:25,720
As expected of the Tower Master.

68
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:27,070
(Heartbroken and in tears.)

69
00:04:28,310 --> 00:04:30,270
(Wangshi Tower Master
has both fame and fortune.)

70
00:04:31,190 --> 00:04:33,360
(Why can she write
such sorrowful poetry?)

71
00:04:35,070 --> 00:04:36,800
(Why does she look so young)

72
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:39,270
(yet seem like an old woman in spirit?)

73
00:04:41,070 --> 00:04:43,240
(Just how many masters
does Wangshi Tower have?)

74
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:44,750
Tower Master,

75
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:46,560
you are the bolt
of lightning in my life,

76
00:04:46,680 --> 00:04:48,240
awakening my ignorant heart.

77
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:50,190
Tower Master,
you are the light of my life,

78
00:04:50,190 --> 00:04:51,750
illuminating my path forward.

79
00:04:51,750 --> 00:04:56,630
- Tower Master!
- Tower Master!

80
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:58,240
(I am electricity, I am light.)

81
00:04:58,240 --> 00:04:59,800
(I am the only myth.)

82
00:05:00,750 --> 00:05:02,800
(Is this what
it feels like to be a celebrity?)

83
00:05:03,870 --> 00:05:07,360
(I feel like I'm floating.)

84
00:05:07,750 --> 00:05:11,720
- Tower Master, you're amazing.
- Tower Master!

85
00:05:12,070 --> 00:05:15,510
- Tower Master!
- Tower Master!

86
00:05:15,630 --> 00:05:18,720
- Tower Master!
- Tower Master!

87
00:05:18,870 --> 00:05:19,870
You are fantastic.

88
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:21,360
(After today,)

89
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,800
(Wangshi Tower
will have everyone's support.)

90
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:26,430
(I'm afraid I can't use force
against her anymore.)

91
00:05:26,430 --> 00:05:27,920
- Tower Master!
- Tower Master!

92
00:05:28,390 --> 00:05:29,240
(Very well.)

93
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:31,310
(It's been a long time since I)

94
00:05:31,310 --> 00:05:33,200
(have encountered
such an interesting enemy.)

95
00:05:33,310 --> 00:05:35,120
Tower Master, I love you!

96
00:05:36,310 --> 00:05:38,360
- Tower Master!
- Tower Master!

97
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:40,070
Look, the Tower Master
released another new poem.

98
00:05:40,070 --> 00:05:41,160
I must take these poems

99
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:42,950
back home to copy down and worship them.

100
00:05:45,870 --> 00:05:47,000
Let me see that.

101
00:05:47,270 --> 00:05:48,800
I couldn't buy it again today.

102
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:49,270
Sure.

103
00:05:49,530 --> 00:05:51,500
Look, even the Tower Master
says it's delicious.

104
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:55,190
Tower Master reviewed the osmanthus cake
from Li's Shop on East Street,

105
00:05:55,390 --> 00:05:57,390
praising it for being
sweet but not greasy,

106
00:05:57,460 --> 00:05:58,560
just like a heavenly pastry.

107
00:05:58,790 --> 00:05:59,870
Quick, look at this section.

108
00:06:00,390 --> 00:06:02,360
It says today
the Tower Master is wearing

109
00:06:02,360 --> 00:06:04,390
the Plain Snow Silk from Yunyi Pavilion,

110
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:07,040
paired with the Black Jade Hairpin
from Molan House.

111
00:06:07,510 --> 00:06:08,430
How elegant.

112
00:06:08,430 --> 00:06:08,870
Yes.

113
00:06:09,660 --> 00:06:11,860
Whatever the Tower Master likes
must be a fine thing.

114
00:06:11,870 --> 00:06:12,560
Let's go buy it quickly.

115
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:13,160
It'll be gone if we're late.

116
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:13,600
Go.

117
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:14,510
Let's go.

118
00:06:17,870 --> 00:06:19,000
Let me see it too.

119
00:06:27,630 --> 00:06:28,560
Hurry.

120
00:06:38,270 --> 00:06:38,950
Tower Master,

121
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:40,830
you have the Midas touch.

122
00:06:41,160 --> 00:06:43,160
With just a single review
of yours in the paper,

123
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:45,720
our imperial merchant shop
is now bustling with customers,

124
00:06:45,730 --> 00:06:46,930
and our income has skyrocketed.

125
00:06:47,630 --> 00:06:49,430
It's just a small amount of money.

126
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:50,240
Yuanzhao,

127
00:06:50,630 --> 00:06:53,160
you need to look further ahead.

128
00:06:56,950 --> 00:06:59,240
(Finally seeing
some return on investment.)

129
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:01,560
Do you know where the biggest source

130
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:03,950
of income for our newspaper comes from?

131
00:07:04,950 --> 00:07:06,390
Please enlighten me, Tower Master.

132
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:08,630
Advertising fees.

133
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:11,680
Smart people already know

134
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:12,750
that our Wangshi Chronicle

135
00:07:12,750 --> 00:07:15,390
can make their products
famous across the land.

136
00:07:15,830 --> 00:07:17,270
But what exactly gets published

137
00:07:17,630 --> 00:07:19,600
is entirely up to us.

138
00:07:19,880 --> 00:07:21,160
Those merchants will spend money

139
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:22,950
to beg us to feature them.

140
00:07:23,750 --> 00:07:24,720
When that time comes,

141
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:27,270
we'll be making money just sitting down.

142
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:31,000
In this way,

143
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:32,800
the lifeblood of all merchants

144
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:34,240
will be held right in our hands.

145
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:37,950
Go on.

146
00:07:38,310 --> 00:07:39,630
Send out invitations far and wide.

147
00:07:40,160 --> 00:07:41,800
Say that I

148
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:43,560
invite the imperial merchants
for a chat.

149
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:44,630
Understood.

150
00:07:53,270 --> 00:07:54,070
Hurry up.

151
00:07:59,360 --> 00:08:00,560
She's cute.

152
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:03,830
It hasn't been easy.

153
00:08:03,830 --> 00:08:05,800
We finally managed to recoup some funds.

154
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:09,070
Now Jiuzhu and the others'
monthly pay is sorted.

155
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:09,920
No way.

156
00:08:12,310 --> 00:08:13,800
With such a small amount of money,

157
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:15,240
even if we pay them,

158
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:16,630
it's just a drop in the bucket.

159
00:08:16,950 --> 00:08:17,600
Besides,

160
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:20,160
we still need to reinvest it
as capital into the newspaper.

161
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:21,830
Once the imperial merchants'
meeting is over

162
00:08:21,830 --> 00:08:24,240
and our advertising
platform business takes off,

163
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:25,160
we'll make a fortune

164
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:26,310
and give them a huge payout.

165
00:08:26,630 --> 00:08:28,600
This is called delayed gratification

166
00:08:28,770 --> 00:08:29,750
and capital compounding.

167
00:08:31,390 --> 00:08:32,870
What if Jiuzhu asks about it...

168
00:08:32,870 --> 00:08:33,530
Hide it from him.

169
00:08:34,550 --> 00:08:35,440
We must hide it.

170
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:36,120
Alright.

171
00:08:36,150 --> 00:08:37,550
Quickly hide these things.

172
00:08:37,550 --> 00:08:37,960
Alright.

173
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:42,840
Just tell them the Second Prince
hasn't settled the payment with us.

174
00:08:59,030 --> 00:08:59,840
Hi.

175
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:03,440
I heard the Second Prince
brought some money over.

176
00:09:07,150 --> 00:09:07,870
No, he didn't.

177
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:09,000
Who said that?

178
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:10,200
Total rumor.

179
00:09:12,150 --> 00:09:14,870
He just brought some
account books for me to audit.

180
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,150
Right, Caiyuan?

181
00:09:18,630 --> 00:09:20,750
Yes, I guess so.

182
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:23,440
You're lying to me.

183
00:09:24,390 --> 00:09:24,670
I...

184
00:09:24,670 --> 00:09:26,080
I can smell the silver.

185
00:09:27,550 --> 00:09:28,750
(Are you a dog or something?)

186
00:09:35,390 --> 00:09:36,630
What's under your butt?

187
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:39,080
What's what?

188
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:52,360
I am the Tower Master!

189
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:53,240
Insolent.

190
00:10:01,870 --> 00:10:02,840
What's this?

191
00:10:08,780 --> 00:10:12,140
♪Snowflakes settle gently
upon your brows♪

192
00:10:12,900 --> 00:10:16,300
♪Your dark hair
brushes across my fingertips♪

193
00:10:17,060 --> 00:10:18,820
♪Your smile♪

194
00:10:19,060 --> 00:10:21,340
♪Melts away the winter snow♪

195
00:10:21,340 --> 00:10:25,020
♪One fleeting glance says more
than a thousand words♪

196
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:28,820
♪Yet I stand before you♪

197
00:10:29,540 --> 00:10:33,380
♪Unable to recognize your eyes♪

198
00:10:33,780 --> 00:10:35,700
♪Though fate tries♪

199
00:10:35,700 --> 00:10:38,300
♪To make us pass each other by♪

200
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:41,940
♪I choose to make our story whole♪

201
00:10:42,180 --> 00:10:43,820
♪Though time slips by♪

202
00:10:43,820 --> 00:10:45,580
♪As day turns into night♪

203
00:10:46,100 --> 00:10:50,140
♪I still remember
our days at Wangshi Tower♪

204
00:10:50,540 --> 00:10:52,940
♪One glance at you lasts a lifetime♪

205
00:10:52,940 --> 00:10:54,700
♪Blessed by fate♪

206
00:10:54,700 --> 00:10:59,860
♪I believe this moment
will last forever♪

207
00:10:59,860 --> 00:11:02,300
♪Your smiling face♪

208
00:11:02,300 --> 00:11:05,140
♪Is the most beautiful poem♪

209
00:11:05,140 --> 00:11:08,780
♪I'd rather spend my days with you♪

210
00:11:09,300 --> 00:11:12,740
♪And wander the world together♪

211
00:11:12,740 --> 00:11:14,100
♪Holding you close♪

212
00:11:14,100 --> 00:11:16,620
♪Envying neither lovers nor immortals♪

213
00:11:16,620 --> 00:11:18,940
♪Your tenderness♪

214
00:11:18,940 --> 00:11:21,820
♪Is the brightest moon♪

215
00:11:21,820 --> 00:11:25,500
♪I'd rather
pledge three lifetimes to you♪

216
00:11:26,020 --> 00:11:29,340
♪Our love will never fade away♪

217
00:11:29,340 --> 00:11:31,780
♪Though heaven and earth grow old♪

218
00:11:32,300 --> 00:11:36,580
♪My heart will remain forever pure♪

219
00:11:46,060 --> 00:11:48,220
♪Your smiling face♪

220
00:11:48,380 --> 00:11:50,980
♪Is the most beautiful poem♪

221
00:11:51,300 --> 00:11:55,140
♪I'd rather spend my days with you♪

222
00:11:55,380 --> 00:11:58,860
♪And wander the world together♪

223
00:11:58,860 --> 00:12:00,180
♪Holding you close♪

224
00:12:00,180 --> 00:12:02,820
♪Envying neither lovers nor immortals♪

225
00:12:02,820 --> 00:12:05,100
♪Your tenderness♪

226
00:12:05,100 --> 00:12:07,940
♪Is the brightest moon♪

227
00:12:07,940 --> 00:12:11,700
♪I'd rather
pledge three lifetimes to you♪

228
00:12:12,140 --> 00:12:15,500
♪Our love will never fade away♪

229
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:18,140
♪Though heaven and earth grow old♪

230
00:12:18,420 --> 00:12:22,540
♪My heart will remain forever pure♪
